1. Šume u Srbiji su veoma važne za očuvanje biodiverziteta. (*šume*) (Forests in Serbia are very important for the preservation of biodiversity.)
2. U proleće, šume *zazelenju* i postaju još lepše. (Forest *green up* in spring and become even more beautiful.)
3. Kada sam bio mali, voleo sam da se igram u *šumi*. (When I was a kid, I loved playing in the *woods*.)
4. Danas smo prošli kroz gustu *šumu* i naišli na divlje jagode. (Today we passed through a dense *forest* and stumbled upon wild strawberries.)
5. Uprkos našim naporima da sprečimo seču, veliki deo *šuma* je i dalje nestao. (Despite our efforts to prevent deforestation, a large portion of the *forests* has still disappeared.)
6. Nadam se da ćemo u budućnosti uspeti da zaštitimo preostale *šume* od nekontrolisane seče. (I hope that in the future, we will be able to protect the remaining *forests* from uncontrolled logging.)
7. Da bi se izgradio novi put, potrebno je iseći deo *šume* koja se nalazi na tom području. (In order to build a new road, a portion of the *forest* located in that area needs to be cut down.)
8. Kada sam ušao u *šumu*, osetio sam miris borova i smreka. (When I entered the *woods*, I smelled the scent of pine and spruce.)
9. Zaštitari šuma često se suočavaju sa problemom ilegalne seče i krivolova. (*šume*) (Forest rangers often face the problem of illegal logging and poaching.)
10. Da bi se sprečile štete od šumskih požara, važno je da se *šume* redovno čiste od suvih grančica i lišća. (To prevent damage from forest fires, it's important to regularly clear *forests* of dry branches and leaves.)